#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.34"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.34:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.34:0.2"
msgid "4. Sumanavagga "
msgstr "4. With Sumanā "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.34:0.3"
msgid "34. Sīhasenāpatisutta "
msgstr "34. With General Sīha "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.39, sc1
msgctxt "an5.34:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.34:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho sīho senāpati yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho sīho senāpati bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then General Sīha went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and asked him, "

msgctxt "an5.34:1.3"
msgid "“sakkā nu kho, bhante, bhagavā sandiṭṭhikaṃ dānaphalaṃ paññāpetun”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, can you point out a fruit of giving that’s apparent in the present life?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an5.34:2.1"
msgid "“Sakkā, sīhā”ti bhagavā avoca: "
msgstr "“I can, Sīha,” said the Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.34:2.2"
msgid "“dāyako, sīha, dānapati bahuno janassa piyo hoti manāpo. "
msgstr "“A giver, a donor is dear and beloved to many people. "

msgctxt "an5.34:2.3"
msgid "Yampi, sīha, dāyako dānapati bahuno janassa piyo hoti manāpo, idampi sandiṭṭhikaṃ dānaphalaṃ. "
msgstr "This is a fruit of giving that’s apparent in the present life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an5.34:3.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, sīha, dāyakaṃ dānapatiṃ santo sappurisā bhajanti. "
msgstr "Furthermore, good people associate with a giver. "

msgctxt "an5.34:3.2"
msgid "Yampi, sīha, dāyakaṃ dānapatiṃ santo sappurisā bhajanti, idampi sandiṭṭhikaṃ dānaphalaṃ. "
msgstr "This is another fruit of giving that’s apparent in the present life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an5.34:4.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, sīha, dāyakassa dānapatino kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggacchati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a giver gains a good reputation. "

msgctxt "an5.34:4.2"
msgid "Yampi, sīha, dāyakassa dānapatino kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggacchati, idampi sandiṭṭhikaṃ dānaphalaṃ. "
msgstr "This is another fruit of giving that’s apparent in the present life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
#. VAR: visārado → visāradova (bj)
msgctxt "an5.34:5.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, sīha, dāyako dānapati yaṃ yadeva parisaṃ upasaṅkamati—yadi khattiyaparisaṃ yadi brāhmaṇaparisaṃ yadi gahapatiparisaṃ yadi samaṇaparisaṃ—visārado upasaṅkamati amaṅkubhūto. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a giver enters any kind of assembly bold and assured, whether it’s an assembly of aristocrats, brahmins, householders, or ascetics. "

msgctxt "an5.34:5.2"
msgid "Yampi, sīha, dāyako dānapati yaṃ yadeva parisaṃ upasaṅkamati—yadi khattiyaparisaṃ yadi brāhmaṇaparisaṃ yadi gahapatiparisaṃ yadi samaṇaparisaṃ—visārado upasaṅkamati amaṅkubhūto, idampi sandiṭṭhikaṃ dānaphalaṃ. "
msgstr "This is another fruit of giving that’s apparent in the present life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an5.34:6.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, sīha, dāyako dānapati kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, when a giver’s body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm. "

#. VAR: idaṃ → idaṃpi (s1-3, pts1) | idampi sīha (mr)
msgctxt "an5.34:6.2"
msgid "Yampi, sīha, dāyako dānapati kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati, idaṃ samparāyikaṃ dānaphalan”ti. "
msgstr "This is a fruit of giving to do with lives to come.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.40, sc7
msgctxt "an5.34:7.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, sīho senāpati bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, General Sīha said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "an5.34:7.2"
msgid "“yānimāni, bhante, bhagavatā cattāri sandiṭṭhikāni dānaphalāni akkhātāni, nāhaṃ ettha bhagavato saddhāya gacchāmi; ahaṃ petāni jānāmi. "
msgstr "“When it comes to those four fruits of giving that are apparent in the present life, I don’t have to rely on faith in the Buddha, for I know them too. "

msgctxt "an5.34:7.3"
msgid "Ahaṃ, bhante, dāyako dānapati bahuno janassa piyo manāpo. "
msgstr "I’m a giver, a donor, and am dear and beloved to many people. "

msgctxt "an5.34:7.4"
msgid "Ahaṃ, bhante, dāyako dānapati; maṃ santo sappurisā bhajanti. "
msgstr "I’m a giver, and good people associate with me. "

msgctxt "an5.34:7.5"
msgid "Ahaṃ, bhante, dāyako dānapati; mayhaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato: ‘sīho senāpati dāyako kārako saṅghupaṭṭhāko’ti. "
msgstr "I’m a giver, and I have this good reputation: ‘General Sīha gives, serves, and attends on the Saṅgha.’ "

msgctxt "an5.34:7.6"
msgid "Ahaṃ, bhante, dāyako dānapati yaṃ yadeva parisaṃ upasaṅkamāmi—yadi khattiyaparisaṃ yadi brāhmaṇaparisaṃ yadi gahapatiparisaṃ yadi samaṇaparisaṃ—visārado upasaṅkamāmi amaṅkubhūto. "
msgstr "I’m a giver, and I enter any kind of assembly bold and assured, whether it’s an assembly of aristocrats, brahmins, householders, or ascetics. "

msgctxt "an5.34:7.7"
msgid "Yānimāni, bhante, bhagavatā cattāri sandiṭṭhikāni dānaphalāni akkhātāni, nāhaṃ ettha bhagavato saddhāya gacchāmi; ahaṃ petāni jānāmi. "
msgstr "When it comes to these four fruits of giving that are apparent in the present life, I don’t have to rely on faith in the Buddha, for I know them too. "

msgctxt "an5.34:7.8"
msgid "Yañca kho maṃ, bhante, bhagavā evamāha: "
msgstr "But when the Buddha says: "

msgctxt "an5.34:7.9"
msgid "‘dāyako, sīha, dānapati kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjatī’ti, etāhaṃ na jānāmi; ettha ca panāhaṃ bhagavato saddhāya gacchāmī”ti. "
msgstr "‘When a giver’s body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.’ I don’t know this, so I have to rely on faith in the Buddha.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.34:7.10"
msgid "“Evametaṃ, sīha, evametaṃ, sīha. "
msgstr "“That’s so true, Sīha! That’s so true! "

msgctxt "an5.34:7.11"
msgid "Dāyako dānapati kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjatīti. "
msgstr "When a giver’s body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an5.34:8.1"
msgid "Dadaṃ piyo hoti bhajanti naṃ bahū, "
msgstr "Giving, you’re loved and befriended by many people. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: yaso ca vaḍḍhati → yasobhivaḍḍhati (bj) | yasassa vaḍḍhati (s1-3, km) | yasaṃ pavaḍḍhati (mr)
msgctxt "an5.34:8.2"
msgid "Kittiñca pappoti yaso ca vaḍḍhati; "
msgstr "You get a good reputation, and your fame grows. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.34:8.3"
msgid "Amaṅkubhūto parisaṃ vigāhati, "
msgstr "A generous man enters an assembly "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.34:8.4"
msgid "Visārado hoti naro amaccharī. "
msgstr "bold and assured. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an5.34:9.1"
msgid "Tasmā hi dānāni dadanti paṇḍitā, "
msgstr "So an astute person, seeking happiness, would give gifts, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.34:9.2"
msgid "Vineyya maccheramalaṃ sukhesino; "
msgstr "having driven out the stain of stinginess. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.34:9.3"
msgid "Te dīgharattaṃ tidive patiṭṭhitā, "
msgstr "They live long in the heaven of the Three and Thirty, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: sahabyagatā ramanti te → sahabyataṃ gatā ramanti (bj) | sahabyatā ramanti te (mr)
msgctxt "an5.34:9.4"
msgid "Devānaṃ sahabyagatā ramanti te. "
msgstr "enjoying the company of the gods. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
#. VAR: cutā → tato cutā (bj)
msgctxt "an5.34:10.1"
msgid "Katāvakāsā katakusalā ito cutā, "
msgstr "Having taken the opportunity to do good, when they pass from here "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: nandanaṃ → nandane (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an5.34:10.2"
msgid "Sayaṃpabhā anuvicaranti nandanaṃ; "
msgstr "they wander radiant in the Garden of Delight. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.34:10.3"
msgid "Te tattha nandanti ramanti modare, "
msgstr "There they delight, rejoice, and enjoy themselves, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.34:10.4"
msgid "Samappitā kāmaguṇehi pañcahi; "
msgstr "provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.34:10.5"
msgid "Katvāna vākyaṃ asitassa tādino, "
msgstr "Doing what the unattached, the poised one says, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Ramanti sagge → kamanti sabbe (s1-3, km) | ramanti sumanā (mr)
msgctxt "an5.34:10.6"
msgid "Ramanti sagge sugatassa sāvakā”ti. "
msgstr "disciples of the Holy One rejoice in heaven.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.34:10.7"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

